<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Learn how AUXO Data Labs collects, uses, and protects your personal information in accordance with privacy regulations."
  lastUpdated="January 10, 2026"
>
  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    Welcome to AUXO Data Labs ("we," "us," "our"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal data when you visit our website, auxodata.com ("Site"), or engage with our marketing channels.
  </p>
  <h3>Legal Entity:</h3>
  <p>
    This Site is owned and operated by Rapple International FZE (trading as AUXO Data Labs), a company registered in the United Arab Emirates. For the purposes of the UAE Personal Data Protection Law (PDPL) and the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), Rapple International FZE is the Data Controller of the personal data collected through this Site.
  </p>
  <h3>Scope of this Policy:</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Website Visitors &amp; Leads:</strong> This Policy applies to data we collect from you directly (e.g., forms, cookies).
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Client Data (Services):</strong> This Policy does NOT apply to data we process on behalf of our business clients ("Client Data") while providing analytics services. Client Data is governed by our Master Services Agreement (MSA) and treated in accordance with our role as a Data Processor.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
  <h3>2.1 Personal Data You Provide</h3>
  <p>
    We collect personal data directly from you when you complete forms on our Site (contact, demo requests, content downloads), subscribe to newsletters, or apply for job opportunities.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Identifiers:</strong> Name, business email, telephone number.</li>
    <li><strong>Professional information:</strong> Job title, company name, industry.</li>
    <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Feedback, inquiries, or specific project details you choose to share.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.2 Data Collected Automatically</h3>
  <p>
    When you visit our Site, we automatically collect technical data via cookies and similar technologies. This includes IP address, browser type, operating system, device identifiers, session duration, and click-stream behavior.
  </p>

  <h3>2.3 Data from Third Parties</h3>
  <p>
    We may receive business contact information from event partners (when you register for an event we sponsor) or public professional networks (like LinkedIn) for B2B marketing purposes, strictly in accordance with applicable laws.
  </p>

  <h2>3. How We Use Your Data &amp; Legal Basis</h2>
  <table class="legal-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Legal Basis (GDPR / PDPL)</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Provide and maintain our Site</td>
        <td>Legitimate Interest (Ensuring security and functionality)</td>
      </tr>
