        <td>Consent / Contractual Necessity (Pre-contractual steps)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Send newsletters &amp; marketing</td>
        <td>Consent (Opt-in) or Legitimate Interest (B2B context)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Analyze trends (Website Analytics)</td>
        <td>Legitimate Interest (Improving our services)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Legal Compliance &amp; Security</td>
        <td>Legal Obligation</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>4. Cookies &amp; Tracking Technologies</h2>
  <h3>4.1 Usage:</h3>
  <p>
    We use cookies to enable essential site functionality, measure performance (Google Analytics), and deliver relevant B2B content.
  </p>
  <h3>4.2 Management:</h3>
  <p>
    On your first visit, you will see a Cookie Banner. You can accept or reject non-essential cookies. You can also disable cookies via your browser settings, though this may affect Site performance.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Disclosure of Your Data</h2>
  <p>
    We share data only when necessary:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> With trusted vendors (e.g., CRM systems, cloud hosting, email marketing platforms) bound by strict confidentiality and data processing agreements.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> If required by law, court order, or government authority (including UAE Data Office).</li>
    <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal data. We do not process "Sensitive Personal Data" (health, biometric, religious) through this Site.
  </p>

  <h2>6. International Transfers</h2>
  <p>
    As a global consultancy, your data may be processed in the UAE, United States, or Europe.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Transfers from EU/UK:</strong> When transferring data outside the EEA to the UAE or other jurisdictions, we rely on Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) or adequacy decisions to ensure your rights are protected.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Data Security &amp; Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We use enterprise-grade security measures—including TLS 1.3 encryption for data in transit and AES-256 for data at rest—along with multi-factor authentication and access controls to protect your data.
  </p>
  <p>
    We retain personal data only as long as necessary:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Contact/Sales Inquiries:</strong> 3 years from last interaction.</li>
    <li><strong>Marketing Data:</strong> Until you unsubscribe (opt-out) or after 2 years of inactivity.</li>
    <li><strong>Website Analytics Data:</strong> 14 months (in accordance with Google Analytics 4 standards).</li>
    <li><strong>Legal Records:</strong> As required by UAE law (typically 5-7 years).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your location (UAE, EU, UK, California), you have rights regarding your data:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access &amp; Correction:</strong> Request a copy of your data or correct errors.</li>
    <li><strong>Erasure ("Right to be Forgotten"):</strong> Request deletion of your data.</li>
    <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Restrict how we process your data.</li>
    <li><strong>Withdraw Consent:</strong> Unsubscribe from marketing at any time.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>How to Exercise Rights:</strong> To exercise these rights, email our Data Protection Officer at <a href="mailto:privacy@auxodata.com">privacy@auxodata.com</a>. We will respond within 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>9. California Residents (CCPA/CPRA)</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell personal information. California residents have the right to request disclosure of data collection practices and the specific pieces of information we hold. You also have the right to non-discrimination for exercising these rights.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Children's Data</h2>
  <p>
    Our Site is a B2B platform intended for professionals. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 16.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Policy to reflect legal or operational changes. The updated version will be indicated by the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    For any privacy-related questions, please contact:
  </p>
  <p>
    Rapple International FZE (t/a AUXO Data Labs)<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@auxodata.com">privacy@auxodata.com</a>
  </p>

